## acr-push-tui environment configuration
#
# The app loads settings from environment variables prefixed with `ACR_PUSH_`.
# You can copy this file to `.env` and fill in values:
#
#   cp .env.example .env
#
# Notes:
# - In interactive TUI mode (`acr-push-tui run`), you can leave these unset and
#   pick values in the UI.
# - In CI mode (`acr-push-tui run --ci`), the required values below must be set
#   (either via CLI flags or environment variables) or the app will fail fast.
#
# Required in CI mode:
ACR_PUSH_ACR_NAME=
ACR_PUSH_ACR_RESOURCE_GROUP=
ACR_PUSH_REPO_NAME=
ACR_PUSH_TAG=
ACR_PUSH_DOCKERFILE_PATH=./Dockerfile
ACR_PUSH_BUILD_CONTEXT=.
#
# Optional (defaults shown):
ACR_PUSH_SKIP_LATEST=false
ACR_PUSH_PLATFORM=
ACR_PUSH_LOG_LEVEL=INFO
